---

<BaseLayout
  title="Video for Tech — Cybersecurity, Fintech, Software, SaaS"
  description="Premium video, motion design and animation for cybersecurity, fintech, software, and SaaS brands. Hard-to-visualise products, made legible."
>
  <SectorHero
    sector="Tech"
    headline="Premium video for hard-to-visualise tech."
    intro="Cybersecurity. Fintech. Software. SaaS. We turn abstract systems into films your sales team, board, and analyst community actually use."
    posterUrl="/videos/sector-tech-poster.jpg"
  />

  <SubsectorNav anchors={subsectorAnchors} />

  <PainPoints
    eyebrow="Why this is hard"
    heading="What enterprise tech buyers actually need."
    points={painPoints}
  />

  <!-- Anchored sub-sector content blocks -->
  <Section id="cybersecurity" spacing="loose">
    <Eyebrow>Cybersecurity</Eyebrow>
    <h2 class="mt-3 max-w-readable">Make the invisible legible.</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-readable text-body text-gray">
      Replace this paragraph with cybersecurity-specific copy: vocabulary, recurring
      content categories (product launches, threat-landscape films, analyst
      briefings, event content), regulatory framing, and named anchor brands.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section id="fintech" spacing="loose" surface="graphite">
    <Eyebrow>Fintech</Eyebrow>
    <h2 class="mt-3 max-w-readable">Trust earned in every frame.</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-readable text-body text-gray">
      Replace with fintech-specific copy: payments, infrastructure, regulated B2B,
      and the brand discipline required for buyers from card networks, banks, and
      processors.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section id="software-saas" spacing="loose">
    <Eyebrow>Software & SaaS</Eyebrow>
    <h2 class="mt-3 max-w-readable">Launch velocity, premium finish.</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-readable text-body text-gray">
      Replace with SaaS copy: product launches, feature explainers, customer
      stories, integration partners, in-app onboarding films, and event content
      at the cadence enterprise marketing teams need.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <SectorCaseGrid
    eyebrow="Selected tech work"
    heading="Films that pass review on the first round."
    cases={cases}
  />

  <Testimonials
    eyebrow="In their words"
    quotes={techQuotes}
  />

  <!-- Studio Access teaser -->
  <Section spacing="loose">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 md:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <Eyebrow>Studio Access</Eyebrow>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-9">
        <h2 class="max-w-readable">Ongoing partnership for tech brands.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-readable text-body text-gray">
          Monthly cadence. Predictable output. Editing, motion, AI cinematic
          generation, animated explainers, product content — scoped to volume.
        </p>
        <Button variant="text" href="/studio-access" class="mt-6">
          See how Studio Access works
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <Section spacing="loose" surface="graphite">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 md:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <Eyebrow>Next step</Eyebrow>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-9">
        <h2 class="max-w-readable">Talk to Szymon about a tech project.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-readable text-body text-gray">
          Every intro call goes through the founder directly.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
          <Button variant="primary" href={contact.calendly}>
            Book a call →
          </Button>
          <Button variant="secondary" href={`mailto:${contact.email}`}>
            Email us
          </Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
